<h1>Case 13 — Smart Residential Surveillance Pods</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Smart Residential Surveillance Pods are AI-enhanced security units placed at entrances of 
residential societies. They monitor visitor movement, detect unusual activity, authenticate residents, 
and alert security personnel instantly using automated analysis and smart algorithms.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Unauthorized individuals entering residential zones without being detected.</li>
    <li>Manual visitor verification causing delays and inaccuracy.</li>
    <li>No system to detect suspicious or abnormal behavior patterns.</li>
    <li>Slow communication between surveillance pods and security patrolling teams.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Store resident details, visitor logs, and authentication data.</li>
    <li><strong>KMP Pattern Matching:</strong> Detects suspicious face patterns or repeated attempts.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Handles entry/exit logs and real-time visitor stream data.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Helps route patrol units for faster security response.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS (Optional):</strong> Scan neighboring pods for possible intrusion patterns.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 16 — Peace, Justice & Strong Institutions</strong>
    <p>Supports safer communities by preventing unauthorized access and improving surveillance.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Builds secure living environments and strengthens community protection.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Promotes use of AI-driven security infrastructure for smart residential zones.</p>
</div>

